This is a NetBeans project for running ToolsUI (Java-NetCDF libraries)

Clone this repository:
git clone git@github.com:asascience/ToolsUI.git

Initialize the submodules (Java-OPeNDAP and THREDDS)
git submodule update

Load the three projects into NetBeans:
netcdf-4.x
opendap-2.2
toolsUI-4.x


Getting opendap-2.2 to build:
Edit the opendap-2.2 project properties (right click on project... Properties)
Under Sources:
Remove all references and add the following folders (your path to ToolsUI may be different)
/ToolsUI/Java-OPeNDAP/src/opendap

You should not have to alter the libraries, they are hopefully
referenced relatively.  If for some reason they are not:
Under Libraries, and the "Compile" tab, add all JARs in the
/ToolsUI/Java-OPeNDAP/lib/ folder.

opendap-2.2 should now build correctly!

Getting netcdf-4.x to build:

Download jpeg2000.jar and move it to:
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/

Edit the netcdf-4.x project properties (right click on project... Properties)
Under Sources:
Remove all references and add the following folders (your path to ToolsUI may be different)
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/common/src/java
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/cdm/src/main/java
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/cdm/src/main/resources


You should not have to alter the libraries, they are hopefully
referenced relatively.  If for some reason they are not:

Under Libraries, and the "Compile" tab, add the following:
The opendap-2.2 project
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/commons-httpclient-3.1.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/ehcache-1.6.0.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/jdom.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/je-4.0.71.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/jna.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/protobuf-java-2.1.0.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/slf4j-api-1.5.6.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/stax-api-1.0.1.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/grib-8.0.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/httpclient-4.1.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/httpcore-4.1.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/unidatacommon.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/visadNoDods.jar

On the "Run" tab, add the following:

/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/commons-codec-1.3.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/commons-logging-1.1.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/jpeg2000.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/slf4j-jdk14-1.5.6.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/bufrTables-2.0.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/unidatacommon.jar

netcdf-4.x should now build correctly!


Getting toolsUI-4.x to build:

Edit the toolsUI-4.x project propderties (right click on project... Properties)
Under Sources:
Remove all references and add the following folders (your path to ToolsUI may be different)
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/ui/src/main/java
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/ui/src/main/resources

You should not have to alter the libraries, they are hopefully
referenced relatively.  If for some reason they are not:

Under Libraries, and the "Compile" tab, add the following:

The opendap-2.2 project
The netcdf-4.x project
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/unidatacommon.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/forms-1.0.7.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/httpcore-4.1.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/httpclient-4.1.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/grib-8.0.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/je-4.0.71.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/lucene.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/commons-httpclient-3.1.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/slf4j-api-1.5.6.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/ehcache-1.6.0.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/jcommon-1.0.15.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/jfreechart-1.0.12.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/jakarta-oro-2.0.8.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/bounce-0.14.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/spring-2.5.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/jdom.jar


On the "Run" tab, add the following:
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/commons-codec-1.3.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/commons-logging-1.1.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/jpeg2000.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/external/slf4j-jdk14-1.5.6.jar
/ToolsUI/THREDDS/lib/release/bufrTables-2.0.jar